.TH HSH 1 "December 2025" "Simple Shell" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
hsh \- a minimal Unix shell implemented in C

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.RI [command " [" arguments "]"]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a minimal Unix command interpreter written in C that reproduces the basic behavior of
.BR /bin/sh .
It allows the execution of Unix commands in both interactive and non-interactive modes.

The shell supports:
.IP \[bu] 2
Executing programs using
.BR execve (2)

.IP \[bu] 2
Interactive mode with a prompt displayed (\fB$\fR)

.IP \[bu] 2
Non-interactive mode (reading commands from standard input)

.IP \[bu] 2
Built-in commands:
.B exit
and
.B env

.IP \[bu] 2
Automatic command lookup in directories listed in the
.B PATH
environment variable

.SH USAGE
.TP
.B hsh
Starts the shell in interactive mode and waits for user commands.

.TP
.B echo "ls" | hsh
Runs the shell in non-interactive mode, reading commands from standard input.

.TP
.B /bin/ls
Executes a command using its absolute path.

.TP
.B ls -l
Executes a command with arguments.

.SH EXIT STATUS
The
.B hsh
shell returns:
.IP \[bu] 2
.B 0
on successful execution

.IP \[bu] 2
.B 127
if the command is not found

.IP \[bu] 2
The exit status of the executed command otherwise

